* Interesting/tricky bots angucken (bes. im Community-Bereich aktiv):
  * ClueBot NG + HBC AIV Helperbots(fighting vandalism)
  * Mr.Z-bot: notifies users directly for users that are most likely spammers
  * HagermanBot: signs unsigned discussion entries (and people were upset about
    that! vgl \cite{MueDoHer2013}
  * CopperBot: DE version of the HagermanBot
  * AvicBot: moves pages from category A to category B, if merge request exist on Categories for Discussion, or removes a category entirely if the request is to empty the category
  * CSDWarnBot: warns users when pages they've created are nominated for speedy deletion
  * AIV Helperbots (Vandalismusbekämpfung)
  * http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/User:MartinBot - vandal fighting bot in the EN Wikipedia

  Other bots with community focus in the DE Wikipedia:
  * GiftBot: removes processed flagged revision requests, disseminates a
    newsletter with new edits on pages
  * Itemsbot
  * xqbot: initially: request speedy deletion of orphaned pages/remains of moved pages;
    2 months later: "correcting double redirects, fixing
    links on disambiguation pages, adding missing references tags in
    articles, and the setting of interwiki-links."

* pywikibot, other bot development frameworks
  https://www.mediawiki.org/wiki/Manual:Pywikibot/redirect.py
* SxWiki PHP framework

